"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483076","Wales Office","false","2016-03-24","<p>The Government's view is that the Directive permits a risk-based approach to the identification of whether an individual is a politically exposed person and, when identified, the Directive enables the application of different degrees of enhanced measures to reflect the risks posed. The Government will be setting out this view in a consultation which will be published shortly.</p><p> </p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2016-03-24T16:51:26.737Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483076/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483076/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483076/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2016-03-21","Money Laundering: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what estimate his Department has made of the number of its Senior Civil Servants who will potentially fall under the provisions of the Fourth EU Money Laundering Directive, 2015/849.","false","Biography information for Sir Charles Walker","Broxbourne","Mr Charles Walker","31796"
