tment has stated throughout the passage of the Bill that current claimants will not be affected and these statements are in the public record.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-03-24T17:07:20.73Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483077/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483077/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483077/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-03-21","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many employment and support allowance claimants with (a) Parkinson's disease, (b) rheumatoid arthritis, (c) motor neurone disease, (d) multiple sclerosis and (e) cystic fibrosis have been (i) placed in the support group, (ii) placed in the work-related activity group and (iii) found fit for work since 2008; and what statements have been made to current claimants of employment and support allowance to inform them that they will not be affected by changes.","false","Biography information for Michelle Donelan","Chippenham","Michelle Donelan","31811"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483078","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-03-24","<p>As confirmed by my right honourable friend the Secretary of State in his statement to the House on 21 March, the proposed changes to PIP will not be going ahead.</p><p> </p><p>We spend around £50bn every year on benefits alone to support people with disabilities or health conditions, with spending on Personal Independence Payment (PIP) and Disability Living Allowance (DLA) having increased by more than £3 billion since 2010. The government is committed to talking to disabled people, their representatives, healthcare professionals and employers to ensure the welfare system works better with the health and social care systems and provides help and support to those who need it most.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","31806 ; 31807 ; 31808 ; 31947","2016-03-24T16:50:05.083Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483078/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483078/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483078/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-03-21","Personal Independence Payment: Disability Aids","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of how many people in each (a) region and (b) constituent part of the UK will be affected by changes to personal independence payments: aids and appliances; and what support he plans to give to those affected.","false","Biography information for Michelle Donelan","Chippenham","Michelle Donelan","31812"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483079","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-03-31","<p>The Department does not hold such information about the disabling condition of people who have applied for Disability Living Allowance. Information on DLA claimants’ disabling condition is only held for those who have entitlement to the benefit.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The information we have for the number of people claiming (i.e. entitled to) Disability Living Allowance, by main disabling condition and geography is published and available at: <a href="https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/default.asp" target="_blank">https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/default.asp</a></p><p> </p><p>Guidance for users can be found at: <a href="https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/home/newuser.asp" target="_blank">https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/home/newuser.asp</a></p><p> </p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","31789","2016-03-31T12:22:34.393Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483079/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483079/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483079/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-03-21","Disability Living Allowance: Inflammatory Bowel Disease","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people diagnosed with inflammatory bowel disease in (a) England and (b) Wales applied for disability living allowance in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","31788"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483080","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-03-31","<p>The Department does not hold such information about the disabling condition of people who have applied for Disability Living Allowance. Information on DLA claimants’ disabling condition is only held for those who have entitlement to the benefit.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The information we have for the number of people claiming (i.e. entitled to) Disability Living Allowance, by main disabling condition and geography is published and available at: <a href="https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/default.asp" target="_blank">https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/default.asp</a></p><p> </p><p>Guidance for users can be found at: <a href="https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/home/newuser.asp" target="_blank">https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/home/newuser.asp</a></p><p> </p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","31788","2016-03-31T12:22:34.47Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483080/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483080/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483080/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-03-21","Disability Living Allowance: Inflammatory Bowel Disease","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people who claim disability living allowance in (a) England and (b) Wales have been diagnosed with inflammatory bowel disease.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","31789"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483081","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-03-29","<p>The information requested is not available.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-03-29T15:03:26.697Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483081/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483081/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483081/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-03-21","Employment and Support Allowance: Inflammatory Bowel Disease","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people diagnosed with inflammatory bowel disease in (a) England and (b) Wales applied for employment and support allowance in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","31790"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483082","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-03-24","<p>As confirmed by my right honourable friend the Secretary of State in his statement to the House on 21 March, the proposed changes to PIP will not be going ahead.</p><p> </p><p>We spend around £50bn every year on benefits alone to support people with disabilities or health conditions, with spending on Personal Independence Payment (PIP) and Disability Living Allowance (DLA) having increased by more than £3 billion since 2010. The government is committed to talking to disabled people, their representatives, healthcare professionals and employers to ensure the welfare system works better with the health and social care systems and provides help and support to those who need it most.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","31807 ; 31808 ; 31812 ; 31947","2016-03-24T16:50:04.877Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483082/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483082/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483082/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-03-21","Personal Independence Payment: Disability Aids","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many in work personal independence payment (PIP) claimants will be affected by his Department's proposed changes to aids and appliances points; and how many such claims will (a) no longer qualify for PIP and (b) receive a reduced PIP payment.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","31806"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483083","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-03-24","<p>As confirmed by my right honourable friend the Secretary of State in his statement to the House on 21 March, the proposed changes to PIP will not be going ahead.</p><p> </p><p>We spend around £50bn every year on benefits alone to support people with disabilities or health conditions, with spending on Personal Independence Payment (PIP) and Disability Living Allowance (DLA) having increased by more than £3 billion since 2010. The government is committed to talking to disabled people, their representatives, healthcare professionals and employers to ensure the welfare system works better with the health and social care systems and provides help and support to those who need it most.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","31806 ; 31808 ; 31812 ; 31947","2016-03-24T16:50:04.957Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483083/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483083/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483083/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-03-21","Personal Independence Payment: Disability Aids","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the number of in work personal independence payment (PIP) claimants who will no longer be able to work as a result of his Department's proposed changes to PIP aids and appliances points.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","31807"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483084","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-03-24","<p>As confirmed by my right honourable friend the Secretary of State in his statement to the House on 21 March, the proposed changes to PIP will not be going ahead.</p><p> </p><p>We spend around £50bn every year on benefits alone to support people with disabilities or health conditions, with spending on Personal Independence Payment (PIP) and Disability Living Allowance (DLA) having increased by more than £3 billion since 2010. The government is committed to talking to disabled people, their representatives, healthcare professionals and employers to ensure the welfare system works better with the health and social care systems and provides help and support to those who need it most.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","31806 ; 31807 ; 31812 ; 31947","2016-03-24T16:50:05.02Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483084/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483084/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483084/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-03-21","Personal Independence Payment: Disability Aids","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many personal independence payment (PIP) claimants in each (a) parliamentary constituency and (b) local authority area will be affected by his Department's proposed changes to aids and appliances points; and what the average reduction in PIP payment per person will be.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","31808"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483085","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-03-29","<p>The number of Employment and Support Allowance (ESA) claimants with Inflammatory Bowel Disease as their main disabling condition, in England is 9,130 and the number for Wales is 730.</p><p> </p><p>Source: DWP 100% data.</p><p> </p><p>Notes:</p><ol><li>Figures are rounded to the nearest 10.</li><li>The data is at August 2015 which is the latest available information.</li></ol><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-03-29T14:48:02.37Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483085/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483085/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483085/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-03-21","Employment and Support Allowance: Inflammatory Bowel Disease","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people who claim employment and support allowance in (a) England and (b) Wales have been diagnosed with inflammatory bowel disease.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","31791"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483086","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-03-24","<p>We are rolling out Personal Independence Payment (PIP) to existing Disability Living Allowance (DLA) claimants in a controlled way. We will continue to monitor performance and will carefully control the number of people we choose to invite to claim PIP each month.</p><p> </p><p>The forecast estimates for the numbers of people in receipt of Disability Living Allowance we currently expect to be awarded PIP, in each year to 2020, are in the table below and may be subject to change:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>2016/17</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2017/18</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2018/19</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2019/20</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>450,000</p></td><td><p>550,000</p></td><td><p>350,000</p></td><td><p>50,000</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em>Notes:</em></p><p><em>Data rounded to the nearest 50,000</em></p><p><em>Includes both adults and children reaching age 16</em></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-03-24T17:18:29.873Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483086/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483086/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483086/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-03-21","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many disability living allowance claimants he expects to transfer to personal independence payment in each year to 2020.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","31891"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483087","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-03-24","<p>The Department is developing the detail of how the funding will be allocated. For 2016/17 we are extending our programme of relationship support provision which will include supporting local authorities to improve the quality of couple or co-parenting relationships and extending the evidence base in this policy area.</p><p>We are also exploring which interventions can maximise the important links between parenting and relationship support.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","31875","2016-03-24T17:32:15.813Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483087/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483087/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483087/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-03-21","Families: Government Assistance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what plans the Government has for the allocation of the £70 million funding for relationship support announced by the Prime Minister on 11 January 2016; and what the timetable will be for the distribution of that funding over the Parliament.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","31880"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483088","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-03-24","<p>The Department is developing the detail of how the funding will be allocated. For 2016/17 we are extending our programme of relationship support provision which will include supporting local authorities to improve the quality of couple or co-parenting relationships and extending the evidence base in this policy area.</p><p>We are also exploring which interventions can maximise the important links between parenting and relationship support.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","31880","2016-03-24T17:32:15.717Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483088/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483088/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483088/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-03-21","Families: Government Assistance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much the Government plans to spend on relationship support in 2016-17; and on what programmes that funding will be spent.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","31875"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483089","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-03-24","<p>A total of £11.2m is forecast to be spent in the full year 2015/16 on relationship support as follows:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Legacy Relationship Support Contracts £7.0m</p><p>Evaluation of Legacy Relationship Support Contracts £0.3m</p><p>Innovation Fund £2.5m</p><p>Evaluation of Innovation Fund £0.5m</p><p>Local Family Offer £0.7m</p><p>Perinatal Pilot £0.2m</p><p><strong>Total £11.2m</strong></p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-03-24T17:11:20.337Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483089/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483089/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483089/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-03-21","Families: Government Assistance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much was spent by the Government on relationship support in 2015-16; and to what programmes that funding was allocated.","false","Biography information for Mr David Burrowes","Enfield, Southgate","Mr David Burrowes","31876"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483090","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-03-24","<p>Cases on the 1993 and 2003 are being selected for closure in groups determined by case characteristics. This process started in July 2014 and is planned to last until the end of 2017. When a case going through this process has its on-going maintenance liability ended, it is then referred for “arrears cleanse”. This process involves checking several elements of the case, to ensure that the final debt balance is stable and validated. This validated debt balance is moved to the 2012 system</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-03-24T17:23:51.457Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483090/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483090/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483090/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-03-21","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 29 February 2016 to Question 27438, on children: maintenance, on what basis those cases have been referred for arrears cleansing or validation.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","31886"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483091","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-24","<p>It is standard Government practice not to announce the number of people approached or the details of candidates.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-03-24T15:30:06.477Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483091/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483091/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483091/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-03-21","Pubs Code Adjudicator","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to the Answer of 18 March 2016 to Question 30693, on the Pubs Code Adjudicator, how many people were approached by (a) his Department and (b) Saxton Bampflyde Limited; and how many of those people (i) previously worked and (ii) work for pub companies.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","31924"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483092","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-30","<p>The Government intends to bring the regulations into force by the end of May 2016.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-03-30T09:53:30.653Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483092/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483092/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483092/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-03-21","Public Houses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, on what date his Department plans to publish the final version of the Pubs Code.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","31914"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483093","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-31","<p>The following table details the total costs for running sites operated by the Skills Funding Agency and Education Funding Agency for the past 5 years:-</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>YEAR</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>SKILLS FUNDING AGENCY</strong> <strong>TOTAL (Million)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>EDUCATION FUNDING AGENCY</strong> <strong>(Million)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>12.0</p></td><td><p>-</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>8.1</p></td><td><p>4.5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>8.3</p></td><td><p>4.6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>7.1</p></td><td><p>4.6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>5.3</p></td><td><p>4.8</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><p>The figures include costs relating to rent, rates, insurance and service charges.</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-03-31T09:54:00.177Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483093/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483093/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483093/answer","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483093/answer/previousversion/53580","Biography information for Nick Boles","26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-03-21","Education Funding Agency and Skills Funding Agency: Operating Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to the Answer of 16 March 2016 to Question 30126, what estimate his Department has made of the total cost of running sites operated by the (a) Skills Funding Agency and (b) Education Funding Agency in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","31935"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483094","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-31","<p>The Pay and Work Rights Helpline (PWRH) was replaced by the Acas helpline from 1st April 2015, meaning that the same data referred to in the FOI referenced above is not available for 2015/16. The table below shows the data on referrals from the PWRH to relevant enforcement authorities for the 2009/10 financial year.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>2009/10*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMRC</p></td><td><p>3000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>EAS</p></td><td><p>820</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HSE</p></td><td><p>290</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>DEFRA</p></td><td><p>440</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>GLA</p></td><td><p>100</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>*The Pay and Work Rights Helpline opened in May 2009</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong>Notes</strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>1. Numbers are rounded to the nearest 10</p><p>2. Calls can be referred to more than one agency so the sum does not amount to the total number of calls referred for the period</p><p>3. Calls referred to agencies includes complaints, complex queries and calls where intelligence was passed to other agencies</p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-03-31T09:51:12.13Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483094/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483094/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483094/answer","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483094/answer/previousversion/53582","Biography information for Nick Boles","26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-03-21","Employment: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, with reference to the Freedom of Information Request release of 1 October 2014, reference BIS/FOI/2014/20352, what the data on referrals is for each 