"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483095","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-24","<p>I refer the hon Member to the Answer to Question UIN <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2016-03-10/30732/" target="_blank">30732</a>.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-03-24T17:01:45.53Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483095/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483095/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483095/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-03-21","Pubs Code Adjudicator","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to the Answer of 18 March 2016 to Question 30732 and the oral contribution of the Minister for Small Business, Industry and Enterprise of 10 March 2016, Official Report, column 425, what the nature of Mr Newby's assistance to departmental officials was in the development and implementation of the Pubs Code.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","31998"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483096","HM Treasury","false","2016-04-01","<p>The latest statistics on the average (median) time taken to resolve challenges, for non-domestic properties by local authority as at 30 September 2015 can be found on the VOA disclosure log in table Average time to resolve challenges, 30 September 2015:</p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/non-domestic-rating-average-time-to-clear" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/non-domestic-rating-average-time-to-clear</a><p> </p><p>The time taken to resolve an appeal can be affected by a number of factors, such as the complexity of the case or whether the case proceeds to be listed for hearing by the independent Valuation Tribunal. Some cases can be held up in litigation or placed on hold at the ratepayer's request.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-04-01T12:54:50.807Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483096/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483096/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483096/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-03-21","Non-domestic Rates: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what average time was taken to hear non-domestic rates appeals in each local authority area in the latest year for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","31992"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483097","HM Treasury","false","2016-03-24","<p>The latest forecasts for the apprenticeship levy by the Office for Budget Responsibility are published in table 2.2 of the Budget 2016 document, which is available on gov.uk.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-03-24T12:31:39.823Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483097/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483097/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483097/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-03-21","Apprentices: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will estimate how much the apprenticeship levy is expected to raise in (a) 2017-18, (b) 2018-19 and (c) 2019-20.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","31999"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483098","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-30","<p>The attached table shows the total number of enquiries made to the Pay and Work Rights Helpline (PWRH) by trade sector and whether the call relates to Employment Agency Standards, the Agricultural National Minimum Wage (NMW), Gangmasters Licensing Authority, Health and Safety Executive or NMW issues, where call topic information is collected, between 2009/10 and 2014/15.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-03-30T14:29:46.273Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483098/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483098/answer","PQ2016-06901.xls","PQ2016-06901.xls","Enquiries to PWRH 2009 - 2015","Enquiries to PWRH 2009 - 2015","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483098/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-03-21","Employment: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to the Answer of 18 March 2016 to Question 30738 on employment: telephone services, what the equivalent data is for each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","31993"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483099","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-01","<p>The appointment panel satisfied itself there were no conflicts of interest when they made recommendations to ministers in relation to the appointment of the Pubs Code Adjudicator.</p><p> </p><p>The Department does not intend to publish any information provided by candidates during this appointment process.</p><p> </p><p>In due course and as is usual practice, the Adjudicator’s office will publish a register of interests.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-04-01T12:52:51.933Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483099/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483099/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483099/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-03-21","Pubs Code Adjudicator","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to the Answer of 18 March 2016 to Question 30688, if he will publish the interests submitted by Mr Paul Newby when he applied for the role of Pubs Code Adjudicator.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","32012"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483100","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-24","<p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>An apprenticeship is a paid job. An apprentice will earn a wage from the start of their degree apprenticeship. The benefits system, which includes council tax exemptions, treats an apprenticeship in the same way as any other job.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-03-24T16:41:15.757Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483100/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483100/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/483100/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-03-21","Apprentices: Council Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, whether learners studying on degree apprenticeship programmes are exempt from council tax.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","32037"
